assylias.jbloomberg

Class IntradayBarRequestBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • assylias.jbloomberg.IntradayBarRequestBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RequestBuilder<IntradayBarData>

    public final class IntradayBarRequestBuilder
extends Object
    This class enables to build an IntradayBarData historical request while ensuring argument safety. Typically, instead of passing strings arguments (and typos) as with the standard Bloomberg API, the possible options used to override the behaviour of the query have been wrapped in enums or relevant primitive types.

    All methods, including the constructors, throw NullPointerException when null arguments are passed in.

    Once the request has been built, the RequestBuilder can be submitted to a BloombergSession.

    This class is not thread safe.

        public IntradayBarRequestBuilder(String ticker,
                         org.joda.time.DateTime startDateTime,

        Creates a RequestBuilder with an event type TRADE. The Builder can be further customised with the provided methods.
        Parameters:
        ticker - a ticker for which data needs to be retrieved - must be valid Bloomberg symbol (for example: IBM US Equity)
        startDateTime - the start of the date range (inclusive) for which to retrieve data
        endDateTime - the end of the date range (inclusive) for which to retrieve data
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if any of the parameters is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the ticker is an empty string or if the start date is strictly after the end date

      • period

        public IntradayBarRequestBuilder period(int period,
                               TimeUnit timeUnit)
        Parameters:
        period - Determine the period of the output. Sets the length of each time bar in the response. Once rounded, it needs to represent a duration between 1 and 1440 in minutes. If omitted, the request will default to one minute. One minute is the lowest possible granularity.
        timeUnit - The time unit in which period is expressed
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if period is not between 1 and 1440 minutes
